Meribel One of several resorts located within France's massive Trois Vallées ski area (others include Courchevel and Val Thorens), Meribel was founded back in 1938 by British Colonel Peter Lindsay – whose family still owns properties around town today! It's easy to see why he fell in love with this place: tree-lined runs cut through beautiful evergreen forests, while chalets made from traditional wood add warmth and character that feels authentic rather than tacky or touristy. Plus, if you time your visit right during peak season weeks such as Christmas week or New Year's Eve celebrations, expect festive fun including live music performances and fireworks displays lighting up the night sky above! Les Gets, France One of the best ski resorts in France, the small and picturesque village of Les Gets started life as a dairy farming village in the 12th century. The ski resort still retains a rustic charm that sets it apart from the larger purpose-built resorts nearby. There are 650km of pistes to choose from in the Portes du Soliel ski area, with something for every level of skier - from beginner zones near the village center to challenging black diamond runs higher up.
